  "title": "Assistant Electrical Design Engineer (Tuas with transport pick up!)",
  "description": "<p><p><p><ul><li>Prepare material requisition lists for job requirements. </li><li>Plan and design electrical switchboards, consoles and control panels according to customer's requirements and company standards. </li><li>Prepare approval drawings, shop drawings, final drawings / documents, short circuit calculations, instruction manuals as required for submission to clients and shop floor production. </li><li>Co-ordinate with clients and consultants on the technical requirements. Attend technical discussions with clients and consultants when required. </li><li>Feed back to Sales & Marketing Department on the changes of technical requirements by clients for claims of additional costs and time. </li><li>Check and follow-up on design and shop drawings with production departments. </li><li>Develop and improve on design of electrical switchboards, consoles and control panels. While taking note of quality, standard, cost effective designs are to be considered. </li><li>Assist and advise Sales & Marketing Department on technical matters, provide technical backup for securing of contracts. </li><li>Carry out other responsibilities as and when assigned by the superiors. </li><li>Follow the procedures of design control, documentation and data control, and quality system of the total Quality Management System</li></ul></p></p></p>",
